**CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing):**

CORS is a browser security mechanism that controls which domains can access your API.

**Problem:** Browser blocks requests from `localhost:3000` (frontend) to `localhost:5000` (API) by default.

**Solution:** Server sends `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header:
```javascript
// Express.js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: 'http://localhost:3000' }));
```

**Headers:** `Access-Control-Allow-Origin`, `Access-Control-Allow-Methods`, `Access-Control-Allow-Headers`.

Here's a complete **React App** with TypeScript:

**1. Setup:**
```bash
npm create vite@latest my-app -- --template react-ts
cd my-app && npm install
```

**2. src/App.tsx:**
```tsx
import { useState } from 'react';
import './App.css';

interface Item {
  id: number;
  text: string;
  completed: boolean;
}

export default function App() {
  const [items, setItems] = useState<Item[]>([]);
  const [input, setInput] = useState('');

  const addItem = () => {
    if (!input.trim()) return;
    setItems(prev => [...prev, { id: Date.now(), text: input.trim(), completed: false }]);
    setInput('');
  };

  const toggleItem = (id: number) => {
    setItems(prev => prev.map(item =>
      item.id === id ? { ...item, completed: !item.completed } : item
    ));
  };

  const deleteItem = (id: number) => {
    setItems(prev => prev.filter(item => item.id !== id));
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ maxWidth: 600, margin: '2rem auto', padding: '0 1rem', fontFamily: 'system-ui' }}>
      <h1>My App</h1>
      <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: 8, marginBottom: 16 }}>
        <input
          value={input}
          onChange={e => setInput(e.target.value)}
          onKeyDown={e => e.key === 'Enter' && addItem()}
          placeholder="Add something..."
          style={{ flex: 1, padding: 8, borderRadius: 6, border: '1px solid #ccc' }}
        />
        <button onClick={addItem} style={{ padding: '8px 16px', borderRadius: 6, background: '#2563eb', color: 'white', border: 'none', cursor: 'pointer' }}>
          Add
        </button>
      </div>
      <ul style={{ listStyle: 'none', padding: 0 }}>
        {items.map(item => (
          <li key={item.id} style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', gap: 8, padding: '8px 0', borderBottom: '1px solid #eee' }}>
            <input type="checkbox" checked={item.completed} onChange={() => toggleItem(item.id)} />
            <span style={{ flex: 1, textDecoration: item.completed ? 'line-through' : 'none', color: item.completed ? '#999' : 'inherit' }}>
              {item.text}
            </span>
            <button onClick={() => deleteItem(item.id)} style={{ background: 'none', border: 'none', color: '#e11d48', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Ô£ò</button>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
      {items.length === 0 && <p style={{ color: '#999', textAlign: 'center' }}>No items yet. Add something above!</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**3. Run it:**
```bash
npm run dev
```

This gives you a working React + TypeScript app with add/toggle/delete functionality.

**Add Tailwind CSS:**
```bash
npm install -D tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite
```

Update `vite.config.ts`:
```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';

export default defineConfig({ plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()] });
```

Replace `src/index.css` with:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```

